 medical professionals but also eleven individuals who either participated in a cardiac rehabilitation program or designed a program of their own. The patients—men and women of varied ages and ethnic backgrounds—relate their own histories, providing insight into the many faces of heart disease and inspiration and hope for other heart attack survivors.The book includes:• risk factors• diets, diagnosis, and treatment• ways to prevent angina from becoming a heart attack• strategies for reversing coronary artery disease• guidelines for choosing a cardiac rehabilitation program• a description of cardiac rehabilitation in action  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aMyocardial infarctionvPopular works. 7aMEDICAL / Cardiology.2bisacsh1 aAdams, Sonny, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBerra, Kathleen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aForsell, Hans, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFox, Jerry, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFriedland, Gerald W., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGardner, Christopher, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGershon, Jacob, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aIbarra, Jose, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJones, Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKoch, Francis H., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKramer, Max, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLouie, Donna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aL’Amoreaux, Helen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMiller, Nancy Hou